{
  "version": 1,
  "_comment": "CANONICAL declarative registry of durable-agent runtimes (DurableSessionRuntime contract). SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH — do not edit the generated copies. Edit THIS file, then run `node scripts/sync-runtime-registry.mjs` to regenerate the build-context-local copies (services/workflow-orchestrator/core/runtime_registry.json for the Python orchestrator reader; src/lib/server/agents/runtime-registry.data.json for the TS BFF reader). The copies exist because each service's Docker build context is its own subdir and cannot COPY this shared file; drift tests (Python + vitest) assert the copies match this canonical. app-ids are NOT frozen here — each reader resolves appIdConfigKey from its own env/config (Python: core.config; TS: process.env[appIdConfigKey] ?? id), so the existing override flow is unchanged. dispatchWorkflowName/bridgeGateToken are the two-name dispatch (dispatched workflow `session_workflow`; bridge-eligibility sentinel `agent_workflow`). Capability flags are advisory until the Phase 3 swap-safety gate consumes them and the Phase 5 conformance harness verifies them (capabilitiesVerified).",
  "dispatchWorkflowName": "session_workflow",
  "bridgeGateTokenConfigKey": "DURABLE_AGENT_CHILD_WORKFLOW_RUN_NAME",
  "defaultRuntimeId": "dapr-agent-py",
